itemDescription: British naturalist, ichthyologist and scientific illustrator (1789-1870)

wikipedia_page.main: Jonathan Couch (15 March 1789 – 13 April 1870) was a Cornish naturalist, the only child of Richard and Philippa Couch, of a family long resident at Polperro, a small fishing village between Looe and Fowey, on the south coast of Cornwall. A blue plaque on the wall of Warren cottage commemorates his birthplace.
